{"type":"data","nodes":[{"type":"data","data":[{"debug":1},true],"uses":{}},{"type":"data","data":[{"zotero":1,"inscriptions":5},{"title":2,"date":3,"citation":4},"Le iscrizioni osche (mamertine) di Messina","1956","\u003Cspan>O. Parlangèli, «Le iscrizioni osche (mamertine) di Messina», \u003Ci>Bollettino Centro di Studi Filologici e Linguistici Siciliani\u003C/i> 4 (1956): 28–38\u003C/span>",[6,120,180,226],{"file":7,"uri":7,"title":8,"status":9,"editionAuthor":11,"type":12,"objectType":16,"material":20,"condition":24,"layoutDesc":26,"handNote":35,"date":49,"places":54,"geo":63,"country":67,"region":68,"settlement":60,"repository":69,"idno":73,"textLang":76,"facsimile":80,"provenance":56,"letterHeights":87,"publications":88,"zotero":98,"keywords":108,"html":119},"ISic001620","I.Sicily inscription 001620",{"_":10},"draft",null,{"_":13,"ana":14,"ref":15},"dedication","#function.dedication","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/88.html",{"_":17,"ana":18,"ref":19},"Block","#object.block","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/189.html",{"_":21,"ana":22,"ref":23},"limestone","#material.stone.limestone","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/66.html",{"ana":25},"#condition.damaged",{"layout":27},{"p":28,"rs":29,"damage":33},"The inscription has five lines of text, damaged on both the left-hand and right-hand sides. Line 3 has no damage to the right-hand side and appears to have only one letter missing from the left-hand side, suggesting that the text was centred on the field.",{"_":30,"ana":31,"ref":32},"chiselled","#execution.chiselled","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1",{"ana":34},"#text_condition.incomplete",{"lettering":36,"dimensions":37},"The inscription is written in the adapted Ionic Greek alphabet which was usually employed to write Oscan in Lucania and Bruttium from around the fourth to the first centuries BC.",[38,45],{"type":39,"l":40,"from":41,"to":42,"h":43,"unit":44},"letterHeight","Lines 1-5","line1","line5","50-60","mm",{"type":46,"l":47,"from":41,"to":48,"unit":44},"interlinear","Interlineation line 1 to 2","line2",{"_":50,"notBefore":51,"notAfter":52,"precision":53},"3rd century BCE",-300,-201,"low",[55,59],{"_":56,"type":57,"ref":58},"Messana","ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462538",{"_":60,"type":61,"ref":62},"Messina","modern","http://sws.geonames.org/2524170",[64],[65,66],38.19394,15.55256,"Italy","Sicily",{"_":70,"role":71,"ref":72},"Museo regionale interdisciplinare di Messina","museum","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/147",{"_":74,"type":75},"A2030","inventory",{"_":77,"mainLang":78,"languages":79},"Oscan","osc",[77],{"n":81,"url":82,"height":83,"width":84,"desc":85,"surfaceType":86},"screen","ISic001620_tiled.tif","2085px","3834px","Photograph J. Prag, 2019-05-02","front",[],[89,90,91,92,93,94,95,96,97],"Buonfiglio Costanzo, 1613, Dell'historia Siciliana terza parte","Gualtherus, 1624 [1625], Siciliæ obiacentium insular. et Bruttiorum antiquæ tabulæ, cum animadversionib","Crawford, 2011, Imagines Italicae. A Corpus of Italic Inscriptions","Vetter, 1953, Handbuch der italischen Dialekte","Morandi, 1982, Epigrafia Italica","Parlangèli, 1956, Le iscrizioni osche (mamertine) di Messina","Orioles, 1992, Bilinguismo e biculturalismo nella Messana mamertina","Rix, 2002, Sabellische Texte : die Texte des Oskischen, Umbrischen und Südpikenischen","Crawford, 2006, The Oscan Inscriptions of Messana",[99,100,101,102,103,104,105,106,107],"QK2SZA3H","ZP8DE8KS","2BHFHCRR","6C5ZKCF2","5U63BQIP","AFQ8FDTW","GGJG3JCZ","SH6KBKBT","G82KT6YE",[109,110,111,13,112,21,113,114,115,116,114,117,118,78],"isic001620","i.sicily inscription 001620",{"_":10},"block","messana","messina","italy","sicily","museo regionale interdisciplinare di messina","oscan","Text encoding: Katherine McDonald, edition source:",{"file":121,"uri":121,"title":122,"status":123,"editionAuthor":11,"type":124,"objectType":125,"material":129,"condition":131,"layoutDesc":133,"handNote":142,"date":149,"places":153,"geo":156,"country":67,"region":68,"settlement":60,"repository":158,"idno":159,"textLang":161,"facsimile":163,"provenance":56,"letterHeights":168,"publications":169,"zotero":172,"keywords":175,"html":119},"ISic001621","I.Sicily inscription 001621",{"_":10},{"_":13,"ana":14,"ref":15},{"_":126,"ana":127,"ref":128},"altar","#object.altar","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/29.html",{"_":130,"ana":22,"ref":23},"limestone (Muschelkalk)",{"ana":132},"#con",{"layout":134},{"p":135,"rs":136,"damage":141},"The inscription is cut into the stucco in the recess and the letters are painted red. Much of the bottom of the stucco has been damaged. “It is highly likely that there was a third line in the [recessed stucco] panel, and quite possible that there were further lines on a block below.” (Crawford 2011)",[137,138],{"_":30,"ana":31,"ref":32},{"_":139,"ana":140},"Rubrication, red coloured","#execution.rubrication.red","",{"lettering":143,"dimensions":144},"The text is written in the adapted Ionic Greek alphabet which was usually employed to write Oscan in Lucania and Bruttium from around the fourth to the first centuries BC.",[145,148],{"type":39,"l":146,"from":41,"to":48,"h":147,"unit":44},"Line 1-2","20",{"type":46,"l":47,"from":41,"to":48,"unit":44},{"_":150,"notBefore":151,"notAfter":52,"evidence":152},"After the Mamertine occupation in 288 BCE, perhaps soon after, and unlikely to be later than the third century.",-288,"textual-context",[154,155],{"_":56,"type":57,"ref":58},{"_":60,"type":61,"ref":62},[157],[65,66],{"_":70,"role":71,"ref":72},{"_":160,"type":75},"A240",{"_":77,"mainLang":78,"languages":162},[77],{"n":81,"url":164,"height":165,"width":166,"desc":167,"surfaceType":86},"ISic001621_tiled.tif","3680px","5520px","I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana",[],[92,170,94,96,91,97,171],"Orsi, 1916, Messana. La necropoli romana di S. Placido e di altre scoperte avvenute nel 1910-1915","Mastelloni, 2005, Messana e i Mamertini",[102,173,104,106,101,107,174],"P49V3TMD","NLNL64ZE",[176,177,178,13,126,179,113,114,115,116,114,117,118,78],"isic001621","i.sicily inscription 001621",{"_":10},"limestone (muschelkalk)",{"file":181,"uri":181,"title":182,"status":183,"editionAuthor":11,"type":184,"objectType":185,"material":186,"condition":187,"layoutDesc":188,"handNote":193,"date":198,"places":201,"geo":204,"country":67,"region":68,"settlement":60,"repository":206,"idno":207,"textLang":209,"facsimile":211,"provenance":56,"letterHeights":216,"publications":217,"zotero":219,"keywords":221,"html":225},"ISic001623","Dedication to Apollo",{"_":10},{"_":13,"ana":14,"ref":15,"cert":53},{"_":112,"ana":18,"ref":19},{"_":21,"ana":22,"ref":23},{"ana":25},{"layout":189},{"p":190,"rs":191,"damage":192},"Two lines with clear vacats above and below, uniform right margin",{"_":30,"ana":31,"ref":32},{"ana":34},{"dimensions":194},[195,197],{"type":39,"l":146,"from":41,"to":48,"h":196,"unit":44},"60-90",{"type":46,"l":47,"from":41,"to":48,"unit":44},{"_":199,"notBefore":151,"notAfter":200,"evidence":152},"mid-3rd century BCE",-225,[202,203],{"_":56,"type":57,"ref":58},{"_":60,"type":61,"ref":62},[205],[65,66],{"_":70,"role":71,"ref":72},{"_":208,"type":75},"A554",{"_":77,"mainLang":78,"languages":210},[77],{"n":81,"url":212,"height":213,"width":214,"desc":215,"surfaceType":86},"ISic001623_tiled.tif","2048px","3072px","I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2006-04-24",[],[92,170,94,171,91,218],"Orioles, 2022, Per una rivisitazione di Vetter 191. Contributo all’interpretazione della formula onomastica",[102,173,104,174,101,220],"SJKD59LV",[222,223,224,13,112,21,113,114,115,116,114,117,118,78],"isic001623","dedication to apollo",{"_":10},"Text encoding: Jonathan Prag, edition source:",{"file":227,"uri":227,"title":228,"status":229,"editionAuthor":11,"type":230,"objectType":231,"material":232,"condition":141,"layoutDesc":233,"handNote":237,"date":244,"places":245,"geo":248,"country":67,"region":68,"settlement":60,"repository":250,"idno":251,"textLang":256,"facsimile":258,"provenance":56,"letterHeights":260,"publications":261,"zotero":262,"keywords":263,"html":119},"ISic002816","I.Sicily inscription 002816",{"_":10},{"_":13,"ana":14,"ref":15},{"_":17,"ana":18,"ref":19},{"_":21,"ana":22,"ref":23},{"layout":234},{"p":235,"rs":236,"damage":141},"The inscription originally consisted of five lines of text, inscribed on two blocks set side by side. The left-hand block has been lost, and the right-hand block has been sawn horizontally into two pieces. There is a large vacat to the right-hand side of each of the five lines, and a vacat above the first line. ",{"_":30,"ana":31,"ref":32},{"lettering":238,"dimensions":239},"The inscription is written in the adapted Ionic Greek alphabet which was usually employed to write Oscan in Lucania and Bruttium from around the fourth to the first centuries BC. Letters are cut in deep square channels.",[240,243],{"type":39,"l":241,"from":41,"to":42,"h":242,"unit":44},"Line 1-5","80-110",{"type":46,"l":47,"from":41,"to":48,"unit":44},{"_":50,"notBefore":51,"notAfter":52,"precision":53},[246,247],{"_":56,"type":57,"ref":58},{"_":60,"type":61,"ref":62},[249],[65,66],{"_":70,"role":71,"ref":72},[252,254],{"_":253,"type":75},"Accascina 239",{"_":255,"type":75},"Accascina 241",{"_":77,"mainLang":78,"languages":257},[77],{"n":81,"url":259,"height":165,"width":166,"desc":167,"surfaceType":86},"ISic002816_tiled.tif",[],[91,97,92,93,94,95],[101,107,102,103,104,105],[264,265,266,13,112,21,113,114,115,116,114,117,118,78],"isic002816","i.sicily inscription 002816",{"_":10}],"uses":{"params":["slug"]}}]}
